                <note rend="inline" type="source">352.1121 Blodgett, Walton/46: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Barcelona (<persName type="from"
                            >Dawson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Palma, Majorca</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-07-21T17:00:00+00:00"
                            >July 21, 1933—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 21—12:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>All the five Americans at liberty under joint bond 20,000 pesetas. Returning
                    Barcelona tonight with the approval of Ambassador.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
